\f0\b\fs52 \cf0 Lentil Sausage Soup\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl240\ql\qnatural

\f1\fs32 \cf2 Serves:  
\b0 \cf0 4 quarts; 8 to 10 servings\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl300\ql\qnatural

\fs36 \cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl320\ql\qnatural

\f0\b\fs44 \cf0 Ingredients\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sl400\ql\qnatural
\ls1\ilvl0
\f1\b0\fs42 \cf0 {\listtext	\'95	}1 pound French green lentils (recommended: du Puy)\
{\listtext	\'95	}1/4 cup olive oil, plus extra for serving\
{\listtext	\'95	}4 cups diced yellow onions (3 large)\
{\listtext	\'95	}4 cups chopped leeks, white and light green parts only (2 {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/leek/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 leeks}})\
{\listtext	\'95	}1 tablespoon minced garlic (2 large {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/clove/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 cloves}})\
{\listtext	\'95	}1 tablespoon kosher salt\
{\listtext	\'95	}1 1/2 teaspoons freshly ground black pepper\
{\listtext	\'95	}1 tablespoon minced fresh {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/thyme/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 thyme}} leaves\
{\listtext	\'95	}1 teaspoon ground cumin\
{\listtext	\'95	}3 cups medium diced {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/celery/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 celery}} (8 stalks)\
{\listtext	\'95	}3 cups medium diced carrots (4 to 6 carrots)\
{\listtext	\'95	}3 quarts Homemade Chicken Stock, recipe follows, or canned broth\
{\listtext	\'95	}1/4 cup tomato paste\
{\listtext	\'95	}1 pound kielbasa, cut in 1/2 lengthwise and sliced 1/3-inch thick\
{\listtext	\'95	}2 tablespoons dry red wine or {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/vinegar/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 red wine vinegar}}\
{\listtext	\'95	}Freshly grated Parmesan, for serving\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl320\ql\qnatural

\f0\b\fs44 \cf0 Directions\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl400\sa140\ql\qnatural

\f1\b0\fs42 \cf0 In a large bowl, cover the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/lentil/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 lentils}} with boiling water and allow to sit for 15 minutes. Drain.\
In a large stockpot over medium heat, heat the olive oil and saute the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/onion/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 onions}}, leeks, garlic, salt, pepper, thyme, and cumin for 20 minutes, or until the vegetables are translucent and tender. Add the celery and carrots and saute for another 10 minutes. Add the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/stock/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 chicken stock}}, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/tomato-paste/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 tomato paste}}, and drained lentils, cover, and bring to a boil. Reduce the heat and {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/simmer/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 simmer}} uncovered for 1 hour, or until the lentils are cooked through and tender. Check the seasonings. Add the kielbasa and red wine and simmer until the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/kielbasa/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 kielbasa}} is hot. Serve drizzled with {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/olive-oil/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 olive oil}} and sprinkled with grated {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/parmesan/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 Parmesan}}\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl320\ql\qnatural

\f0\b\fs44 \cf0 Homemade Chicken Stock:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sl400\ql\qnatural
\ls2\ilvl0
\f1\b0\fs42 \cf0 {\listtext	\'95	}3 (5-pound) chickens\
{\listtext	\'95	}3 large onions, unpeeled and quartered\
{\listtext	\'95	}6 carrots, unpeeled and halved\
{\listtext	\'95	}4 celery stalks with leaves, cut in thirds\
{\listtext	\'95	}4 {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/parsnip/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 parsnips}}, unpeeled and cut in 1/2, optional\
{\listtext	\'95	}20 sprigs fresh {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/parsley/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 flat-leaf parsley}}\
{\listtext	\'95	}15 sprigs fresh thyme\
{\listtext	\'95	}20 sprigs fresh dill\
{\listtext	\'95	}1 head {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/garlic/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 garlic}}, unpeeled and cut in 1/2 crosswise\
{\listtext	\'95	}2 tablespoons kosher salt\
{\listtext	\'95	}2 teaspoons whole black peppercorns\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl400\sa140\ql\qnatural
\cf0 Place the chickens, onions, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/carrot/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 carrots}}, celery, parsnips, parsley, thyme, dill, garlic, salt, and {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/peppercorn/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 peppercorns}} in a 16 to 20-quart stockpot with 7 quarts of water and bring to a boil. Skim the surface as needed. Simmer uncovered for 4 hours. {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/strain/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 Strain}} the entire contents of the pot through a {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/colander/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 colander}}, discarding the chicken and vegetables, and chill. Discard the hardened fat, and then pack the broth in quart containers.\
Yield: 6 quarts\
